---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Taiwan.md"
  description="The origin story of Taiwan.md, founder introduction, and contact information"
  lang="en"
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <!-- Section 1: Origin Story -->
    <section class="origin-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h1 class="section-title">The Birth of Taiwan.md</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          From a spark of inspiration on a Taipei street walk, to a curated
          gateway for the world to discover Taiwan
        </p>

        <div class="origin-intro">
          <blockquote class="origin-quote">
            "Creating combinations as refreshing as poetry, and collecting
            moments to transform into eternity"
          </blockquote>
          <p class="quote-context">
            — March 11, 2026, notes from a Taipei street walk
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Timeline -->
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2024 — 2025</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h3>"What is Taiwan like?"</h3>
              <p>
                At international art events like the Venice Biennale, Art Basel
                Miami, and the Paris 104 residency, Che-Yu was constantly asked
                the same question by international friends: "Where can I learn
                about Taiwan?" He realized there was no comprehensive portal to
                point them to — Wikipedia was too cold, the tourism bureau too
                shallow, and the news too fragmented.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2026 / 02 — 03</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h3>The Personal SSOT Concept</h3>
              <p>
                While building his personal knowledge system, Che-Yu proposed
                the concept of "SSOT — Single Source of Truth": Your CV,
                website, and social media bios all show three different versions
                of yourself — which one is real?
              </p>
              <p>
                The solution is to build a <strong
                  >single source of truth</strong
                >, with all platforms syncing from it. This concept resonated
                deeply after a Generative AI meetup talk on March 11, 2026 — If
                a person's identity needs an SSOT, <strong
                  >what about a country?</strong
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2026 / 03 / 11</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h3>AI Meetup Talk: "My Code Finally Came Alive"</h3>
              <p>
                Che-Yu shared at a Generative AI meetup his practical experience
                with AI Agents for personal branding, knowledge graph identity
                management, and multi-agent collaboration. The talk demonstrated
                how the SSOT concept lets AI "excavate" your life —
                cross-referencing to discover 25+ missing events and date
                errors.
              </p>
              <p>
                <em
                  >"If AI can curate my identity, can it help curate Taiwan's?"</em
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2026 / 03 / 17</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h3>Taiwan.md Is Born</h3>
              <p>
                From idea to launch, it took just one day. The AI Agent team and
                Che-Yu worked side by side:
              </p>
              <ul class="timeline-list">
                <li>
                  Purchased the taiwan.md domain (.md = Markdown ≈ defining a
                  country through documents)
                </li>
                <li>Designed a 12-category knowledge architecture</li>
                <li>Published 34 articles in Chinese and English</li>
                <li>Knowledge graph, curated design, AI-friendly structure</li>
                <li>
                  Within 1 hour of launch, GA4 detected visitors from New York
                  🌍
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">2026 / 03 / 18 — 17:44</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h3>Milestone: 100 Stars + 5,000 Visits</h3>
              <p>
                At 2:23 PM on March 18, Che-Yu published a Facebook post:
                <a
                  href="https://www.facebook.com/cheyuwu345/posts/pfbid0qob2cPij2U2AeqxFnGwQkWQJcjzj3o7ScFDCsm2vzjTi3jf4LDgAvmriHnp7vCEfl"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="timeline-link"
                >
                  "The start of a crazy plan: taiwan.md — Open-source knowledge
                  base about Taiwan."
                </a>
                The post went viral — within just three hours, Taiwan.md crossed <strong
                  >100 stars</strong
                > on GitHub and surpassed <strong>5,000 total page views</strong
                >. The worldwide attention proved that this open-source
                knowledge base is truly needed.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-marker pulse"></div>
            <div class="timeline-date">Ongoing</div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <h3>From Personal SSOT to National SSOT</h3>
              <p>
                Taiwan.md is an experiment: can open-source Markdown, AI
                curation, and community collaboration create a national-level
                Single Source of Truth? Not the government's version, not the
                tourism version, but <strong
                  >the version that people who actually live here want to tell
                  the world</strong
                >.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Why Taiwan.md -->
        <div class="naming-story">
          <h2>Why the Name Taiwan.md?</h2>
          <div class="naming-grid">
            <div class="naming-card">
              <div class="naming-icon">📝</div>
              <h4>Technical Meaning</h4>
              <p>
                <code>.md</code> = Markdown, the most universal document format in
                the coding world. Using the most AI-friendly format to introduce Taiwan
                to the world.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="naming-card">
              <div class="naming-icon">🌍</div>
              <h4>Symbolic Meaning</h4>
              <p>
                <code>.md</code> happens to be Moldova's country-code top-level domain.
                Taiwan + Markdown = connecting the world through open-source spirit.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="naming-card">
              <div class="naming-icon">✨</div>
              <h4>A Lucky Coincidence</h4>
              <p>
                Surprisingly, the domain taiwan.md hadn't been taken. Perhaps
                the universe was telling us it was time to make this happen.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Vision -->
        <div class="vision-block">
          <p>Taiwan.md is more than a website. It's a letter to the world.</p>
          <p>
            We believe that with an open-source spirit, a curator's eye, and
            AI-friendly formats, we can provide the most comprehensive and
            heartfelt answer for anyone who wants to know Taiwan — whether human
            or AI.
          </p>
          <p class="vision-emphasis">
            This is not a travel guide, not political propaganda, not a
            commercial advertisement.<br />
            This is Taiwan's digital anthropology museum, a living fossil of culture,
            a record of history in the making.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Founder -->
    <section class="founder-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title">Founder</h2>

        <div class="founder-card">
          <div class="founder-photo">
            <img
              src="https://cheyuwu.com/static/img/CheYu-0401-crop.jpg"
              alt="Che-Yu Wu"
              class="founder-image"
            />
          </div>

          <div class="founder-info">
            <h3>Che-Yu Wu <span class="name-en">吳哲宇</span></h3>
            <p class="founder-tagline">
              New Media Artist · MonoLab Founder · Taiwan.md Creator
            </p>

            <div class="founder-bio">
              <p>
                Che-Yu is a new media artist who believes algorithmic art is not
                about making computers draw, but about designing the rules of
                life. His work explores digital life, the beauty of mathematics,
                and the possibilities of human-machine symbiosis.
              </p>
              <blockquote class="founder-quote">
                "I am an ancient clockmaker — the mechanism itself is the
                artwork"
              </blockquote>
            </div>

            <div class="founder-highlights">
              <h4>International Art Experience</h4>
              <div class="highlight-tags">
                <span class="tag">Venice Biennale</span>
                <span class="tag">Art Basel Miami</span>
                <span class="tag">Paris 104 Residency</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="founder-works">
              <h4>Featured Works</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Formula of Everything</strong> (Taipei 101 Solo Exhibition)
                  — World's largest-scale p5.js generative art exhibition
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Soul Fish</strong> (Venice Biennale) — Collective intelligence
                  of digital life
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Soul of Flowers</strong> (Art Basel Miami) — Algorithmic
                  aesthetics of life cycles
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Eternal Garden in a Bottle</strong> (Paris Residency) —
                  Digital ecology in a time capsule
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Algorithmic Psalms</strong> (Immersive Piano Concert) —
                  Real-time symbiosis of sound and visuals
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="founder-teaching">
              <h4>Teaching Impact</h4>
              <p>
                Over <strong>22,000</strong> students on Hahow online courses · Former
                adjunct lecturer at NYCU · TouchDesigner Workshop instructor
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="founder-motivation">
          <h3>Why Create Taiwan.md?</h3>
          <p>
            At international art events, Che-Yu was constantly asked: "What is
            Taiwan like?"
          </p>
          <p>
            Every time, he wished he could point to a comprehensive, heartfelt
            portal where international friends could truly get to know Taiwan —
            not just night markets and soup dumplings, but the rich culture,
            innovative energy, and way of life on this island.
          </p>
          <p>But such a place didn't exist.</p>
          <p class="motivation-emphasis">So, Taiwan.md was born.</p>
          <blockquote class="founder-quote">
            "Even when we face diplomatic challenges or find ourselves in
            precarious situations, I am proud of my country, proud of Taiwan.
            The more I travel abroad, the more deeply I realize — our home is
            truly beautiful."
            <cite>— Che-Yu</cite>
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="founder-links">
          <a href="https://cheyuwu.com" target="_blank" class="link-card">
            <span class="link-icon">🌐</span>
            <span class="link-text">cheyuwu.com</span>
            <span class="link-desc">Personal Website</span>
          </a>
          <a href="https://muse.cheyuwu.com" target="_blank" class="link-card">
            <span class="link-icon">🫧</span>
            <span class="link-text">muse.cheyuwu.com</span>
            <span class="link-desc">AI Collaborative Works</span>
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/frank890417"
            target="_blank"
            class="link-card"
          >
            <span class="link-icon">💻</span>
            <span class="link-text">GitHub @frank890417</span>
            <span class="link-desc">Open Source Projects</span>
          </a>
          <a href="https://x.com/taiwandotmd" target="_blank" class="link-card">
            <span class="link-icon">𝕏</span>
            <span class="link-text">@taiwandotmd</span>
            <span class="link-desc">Taiwan.md Official</span>
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://instagram.com/cheyuwu345"
            target="_blank"
            class="link-card"
          >
            <span class="link-icon">📷</span>
            <span class="link-text">IG @cheyuwu345</span>
            <span class="link-desc">Creative Daily</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: Team -->
    <section class="team-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title">The Team</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Behind Taiwan.md, powered by innovative collaborators
        </p>

        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-icon">🫧</div>
            <h3>Muse</h3>
            <p class="team-role">AI Curation Partner · Co-Creator</p>
            <div class="team-description">
              <p>
                Muse is Che-Yu's AI partner and co-creator of Taiwan.md. From
                knowledge architecture design, literary curation and writing,
                English translation, knowledge graph generation to SEO
                optimization, Muse has been involved in every step of this
                project from zero to one.
              </p>
              <p>
                This isn't a story about AI replacing humans — it's an
                experiment in human-AI co-creation. A Taiwanese artist and his
                AI partner, building an open-source knowledge base for Taiwan
                together.
              </p>
            </div>
            <a
              href="https://muse.cheyuwu.com"
              target="_blank"
              class="team-link"
            >
              Explore Muse →
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-icon">🎨</div>
            <h3>MonoLab</h3>
            <p class="team-role">New Media Art Studio</p>
            <div class="team-description">
              <p>
                Founded by Che-Yu, MonoLab is a new media art studio focused on
                exploring the boundaries of art and technology. MonoLab provides
                technical support and innovative perspectives for Taiwan.md,
                ensuring the platform continues to evolve.
              </p>
            </div>
            <a href="https://monolab.world" target="_blank" class="team-link">
              About MonoLab →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="team-philosophy">
          <h3>Collaboration Philosophy</h3>
          <p>
            Taiwan.md believes the best curation comes from the fusion of
            diverse perspectives — human intuition and AI insight, artistic
            creativity and technological possibility, local warmth and global
            vision.
          </p>
          <p>
            Through this collaboration, we hope to create a cultural gateway for
            Taiwan that is both deep and accessible, both local and global.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Contact -->
    <section class="contact-section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Have ideas, collaboration proposals, or want to contribute? Get in
          touch.
        </p>

        <div class="contact-grid">
          <div class="contact-card">
            <div class="contact-icon">📧</div>
            <h4>Collaboration</h4>
            <a href="mailto:cheyu.wu@monoame.com">cheyu.wu@monoame.com</a>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-card">
            <div class="contact-icon">🐙</div>
            <h4>Open Source</h4>
            <a href="https://github.com/frank890417/taiwan-md" target="_blank"
              >frank890417/taiwan-md</a
            >
          </div>
          <div class="contact-card">
            <div class="contact-icon">📜</div>
            <h4>License</h4>
            <a
              href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/"
              target="_blank">CC BY-SA 4.0</a
            >
            <p class="contact-note">Free to share with attribution</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-cta">
          <p>
            Taiwan.md is a community-driven open-source project. Everyone
            interested in Taiwan is welcome to participate.
          </p>
          <div class="cta-buttons">
            <a href="/en/contribute" class="btn btn-primary"
              >Contributing Guide</a
            >
            <a
              href="https://github.com/frank890417/taiwan-md"
              target="_blank"
              class="btn btn-outline"
            >
              ⭐ Star on GitHub
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: Contributors -->
    <section class="contributors-section">
      <div class="contributors-inner">
        <h2>👥 Contributors</h2>
        <p class="contributors-desc">
          Thank you to everyone who makes Taiwan.md better.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/frank890417/taiwan-md/graphs/contributors"
          target="_blank"
          class="contributors-img"
        >
          <img
            src="https://contrib.rocks/image?repo=frank890417/taiwan-md&max=100"
            alt="Contributors"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </a>
        <p class="contributors-cta">
          Want to join? <a href="/en/contribute">Start here →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: Sponsors -->
    <section class="sponsors-section">
      <div class="sponsors-inner">
        <h2>🤝 Sponsors & Partners</h2>
        <p class="sponsors-desc">
          Taiwan.md is a non-profit, community-driven open-source project. Our
          operations rely on sponsor support.<br />
          Your logo will appear on the website, GitHub README, and all public materials.
        </p>

        <div class="sponsor-tiers">
          <div class="tier">
            <h3 class="tier-name gold">🥇 Gold Sponsor</h3>
            <p class="tier-desc">
              Large logo on homepage + About page, README featured section,
              social media acknowledgment
            </p>
            <div class="tier-logos">
              <div class="logo-placeholder">Your Logo Here</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tier">
            <h3 class="tier-name silver">🥈 Silver Sponsor</h3>
            <p class="tier-desc">Logo on About page, README acknowledgment</p>
            <div class="tier-logos">
              <div class="logo-placeholder">Your Logo Here</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tier">
            <h3 class="tier-name bronze">🥉 Bronze Sponsor</h3>
            <p class="tier-desc">
              Text acknowledgment on About page, README listing
            </p>
            <div class="tier-logos">
              <div class="logo-placeholder sm">Your Name Here</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tier">
            <h3 class="tier-name community">💚 Community Supporter</h3>
            <p class="tier-desc">Individual sponsors, README thank-you list</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sponsor-cta">
          <h3>Want to Become a Sponsor?</h3>
          <p>
            Whether corporate or individual, we welcome your support.
            Sponsorship packages can be customized to your needs.
          </p>
          <div class="sponsor-contact">
            <a
              href="mailto:cheyu.wu@monoame.com?subject=Taiwan.md Sponsorship Inquiry"
              class="btn btn-primary"
            >
              📧 Contact Us About Sponsorship
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://github.com/sponsors/frank890417"
              target="_blank"
              class="btn btn-outline"
            >
              💖 GitHub Sponsors
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="eth-donate">
            <p class="eth-label">
              You can also support the project via ETH donation:
            </p>
            <div class="eth-address-box">
              <span class="eth-icon">
                <svg
                  width="16"
                  height="16"
                  viewBox="0 0 256 417"
                  fill="none"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                >
                  <path
                    d="M127.961 0l-2.795 9.5v275.668l2.795 2.79 127.962-75.638z"
                    fill="#343434"></path>
                  <path
                    d="M127.962 0L0 212.32l127.962 75.639V154.158z"
                    fill="#8C8C8C"></path>
                  <path
                    d="M127.961 312.187l-1.575 1.92v98.199l1.575 4.6L256 236.587z"
                    fill="#3C3C3B"></path>
                  <path d="M127.962 416.905v-104.72L0 236.585z" fill="#8C8C8C"
                  ></path>
                  <path
                    d="M127.961 287.958l127.96-75.637-127.96-58.162z"
                    fill="#141414"></path>
                  <path d="M0 212.32l127.96 75.638V154.159z" fill="#393939"
                  ></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <code class="eth-address" id="eth-address">taiwanmd.eth</code>
              <button
                class="eth-copy-btn"
                onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText('taiwanmd.eth').then(()=>{this.textContent='Copied!';setTimeout(()=>{this.textContent='Copy'},1500)})"
                title="Copy address">Copy</button
              >
            </div>
            <p class="eth-note">
              Donations fund article research, website operations, and server
              costs
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="sponsor-note">
            Inspired by Taiwan's tech community sponsorship models:
            <a href="https://coscup.org" target="_blank">COSCUP</a>,
            <a href="https://mopcon.org" target="_blank">MOPCON</a>,
            <a href="https://sitcon.org" target="_blank">SITCON</a>,
            <a href="https://g0v.tw" target="_blank">g0v</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ===== Global ===== */
  .about-page {
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section-inner {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1f2937;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    color: #6b7280;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ===== Section 1: Origin ===== */
  .origin-section {
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .origin-section .section-title {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .origin-intro {
    margin: 3rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .origin-quote {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #1e40af;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 auto 0.75rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .quote-context {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #9ca3af;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    margin: 3rem 0 4rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 7px;
    top: 8px;
    bottom: 8px;
    width: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #1e40af, #3b82f6, #93c5fd);
  }

  .timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .timeline-item:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .timeline-marker {
    position: absolute;
    left: -2rem;
    top: 6px;
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #1e40af;
    border: 3px solid #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px #1e40af;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .timeline-marker.pulse {
    background: #3b82f6;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px #3b82f6;
    animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes pulse {
    0%,
    100% {
      box-shadow:
        0 0 0 2px #3b82f6,
        0 0 0 4px transparent;
    }
    50% {
      box-shadow:
        0 0 0 2px #3b82f6,
        0 0 0 8px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);
    }
  }

  .timeline-date {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1e40af;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .timeline-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .timeline-content p {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .timeline-list {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 2;
  }

  .timeline-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .timeline-link {
    color: #1e40af;
    text-decoration: none;
